  "prompt": "What is repayment credit?",
  "response": "Repayment credit, also known as an installment loan or amortizing loan, is a type of credit where the borrower receives a lump sum of money and repays it in fixed, regular payments over a predetermined period. These payments typically include both principal and interest.\n\nKey characteristics of repayment credit include:\n\n1. Fixed payment schedule\n- Regular monthly payments\n- Predetermined loan term\n- Consistent payment amount\n\n2. Types of repayment credit\n- Personal loans\n- Mortgage loans\n- Auto loans\n- Student loans\n- Home equity loans\n\n3. Repayment structure\n- Payments include principal and interest\n- Interest is usually calculated on the remaining balance\n- Early payments mostly cover interest, later payments cover more principal\n\n4. Benefits\n- Predictable payment amounts\n- Clear loan term\n- Helps build credit history\n- Lower interest rates compared to revolving credit\n\n5. Considerations\n- Total interest paid over loan term\n- Potential prepayment penalties\n- Credit score impact\n- Fixed vs. variable interest rates\n\nRepayment credit differs from revolving credit (like credit cards), where the balance and payment can vary each month.",
